# Git Commit Guidelines

## Commit Size Enforcement
- Maximum 200 lines changed per commit
- Split large changes into logical chunks
- Each commit should be independently testable

## AI-Generated Code Review Checklist
- Verify no code duplication (DRY principle)
- Check for proper error handling
- Ensure consistent coding style
- Validate security best practices
- For JavaScript files only: ensure JSDoc added/updated for all changed functions/classes/modules
- For JavaScript files only: validate that `@param`/`@returns` tags match implementation signatures
